{
  "texts": [
    "As shown in Table 1 (MD17), Table 2 (rMD17), and Table 3 (MD22), it is remarkable that ViSNet outperformed the compared algorithms for both small (MD17 and rMD17) and large molecules (MD22) with the lowest mean absolute errors (MAE) of predicted energy and forces.",
    "On the one hand, compared with PaiNN, ET, and GemNet, ViSNet incorporated more geometric information and made full use of geometric information in ViS-MP, which contributes to the performance gains.",
    "On the other hand, compared with NequIP, Allegro, SO3KRATES, MACE, etc., ViSNet testified the effect of introducing spherical harmonics in the RGC module.",
    "As shown in Table 4, ViSNet also achieved superior performance for chemical property predictions on QM9.",
    "It outperformed the compared algorithms for 9 of 12 chemical properties and achieved comparable results on the remaining properties."
  ]
}